ZH: 他一直对老板的无礼行为视而不见。
EN: He always turns a blind eye to his boss's rude behavior.

ZH: 她选择了视而不见自己身体的警告信号。
EN: She chose to ignore the warning signals from her body.

ZH: 这位领导视而不见底下员工的工作质量。
EN: This leader turns a blind eye to the quality of work from his subordinates.

ZH: 我们不能再对环境问题视而不见了。
EN: We can no longer ignore environmental issues.

ZH: 这个问题已经存在很久，但政府一直视而不见。
EN: This issue has been around for a long time, but the government has turned a blind eye to it.

ZH: 父母对孩子的错误行为视而不见，这不利于他们的成长。
EN: Parents turning a blind eye to their children's misbehavior is not conducive to their growth.

ZH: 老板视而不见员工的疲劳，导致工作效率下降。
EN: The boss turning a blind eye to the fatigue of the employees resulted in a decrease in work efficiency.

ZH: 我们不能再视而不见这个社会问题。
EN: We can no longer turn a blind eye to this social issue.

ZH: 这样视而不见问题只会让事情变得更糟。
EN: Ignoring the problem like this will only make things worse.

ZH: 他总是视而不见自己身上的缺点。
EN: He always turns a blind eye to his own flaws.

ZH: 我们不能只因为困难而视而不见解决办法。
EN: We cannot simply ignore solutions just because they are difficult.

ZH: 这个国家不能再视而不见贫困问题了。
EN: This country can no longer ignore poverty issues.

ZH: 领导视而不见员工的建议，导致决策错误。
EN: The leader turned a blind eye to the suggestions from the employees, leading to wrong decisions.

ZH: 不要因为冲突而视而不见合作的机会。
EN: Don't turn a blind eye to opportunities for cooperation just because there are conflicts.

ZH: 我们不能再对孩子的学习困难视而不见。
EN: We can no longer ignore the learning difficulties of the children.

ZH: 忽略这个问题只会导致更多的麻烦，我们不能视而不见。
EN: Ignoring this problem will only lead to more trouble, we cannot turn a blind eye to it.

ZH: 这位老师视而不见学生之间的欺凌行为。
EN: This teacher turns a blind eye to bullying among students.

ZH: 不要再视而不见你的错误，要认真面对。
EN: Do not turn a blind eye to your mistakes anymore, face them seriously.

ZH: 这个国家政府视而不见人民的诉求。
EN: The government of this country turns a blind eye to the demands of the people.

ZH: 我们不能对社会不公平视而不见。
EN: We cannot turn a blind eye to social injustice.
